Chess Game READ_ME
Isabelle Plaisance 

This is a simple single player chess game in Python using Tkinter for GUI. It has features such as:

-Full Chess Rules: Pieces move according to standard chess rules (pawn, rook, knight, bishop, queen, king).
-Check & Checkmate Detection: Correctly detects when a king is in check or checkmate.
-Stalemate Detection: Detects when a player has no legal moves but is not in check.
-Pawn Promotion: Pawns are automatically promoted to a queen when reaching the opposite end.
-Castling & En Passant: Basic castling and en passant moves supported.
-AI Opponent: Simple AI that plays legal moves for black.
-GUI: Tkinter-based graphical board with emojis for chess pieces.
Legal Move Highlights: Shows available moves for the selected piece.

Run the game by running the Chess_game.py file. 

To play: click on a white piece to select it. Click on one of the valid destination squares to move (it will have a black dot on the options). Ai will automatically make its move after you. Game has status messages on the bottom such as "White to move" and "Check" "Checkmate" and "stalemate"

chess_game.py: game logic and GUI
test_chess_game.py: unit tests for game logic
